      <h1 class='title'>Restrictions on making of orders under this Schedule: welfare of children</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c311GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_311gc' title='Col. 311GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c311GC' name='column_311gc' href='#column_311gc' rel='bookmark'>311GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03980'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_591' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        45 If&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) an application is made by a civil partner for an order under Part 1, 2 or 3, and</li>
        <li>(b) there is a child of the family who is under 18,</li></ol>
        the court must not dismiss or make a final order on the application until it has decided whether to exercise any of its powers under the Children (Northern Ireland) Order 1995 (S.I. 1995/755 (N.I. 2)) with respect to the child.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
